dataIdInfo.idAbs: The file name for this dataset is "afg_admbnda_adm0_agcho_20180522". The structure of the attribute table and field names have been modified to provide consistent notation across the CODs.

Consts.useLimit: This dataset is strictly for humanitarian purposes.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This spatial dataset provides the delimitation and composition of the Afghanistan national boundary and forms one of the Common Operational Datasets (COD) for the humanitarian community. It comprises one national boundary, and is attributed with the country names in Dari and English.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Source: Afghanistan Geodesy and Cartography Head Office (AGCHO). AGCHO and the Independent Directorate for Local Governance (IDLG) are recognised as the sole authoritative source for legal and technical issues related to the delimitation of administrative boundaries, composition, and division of the administrative units of Afghanistan as per the following references: 1) Letter between AGCHO and the President's Office (dated 5 March 2007); and 2) Joint statement from IDLG and AGCHO (dated 26 March 2012).

dataLineage.statement: Layer was sent as a shapefile to ITOS in an email from the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
